commText: Prithvi Shaw and Fraser-McGurk are at the crease. Prithvi Shaw is on strike. Azmatullah will open the attack

Azmatullah to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, beautifully played, Shaw is off and running - pitched up around off, Shaw lets the ball, gets on top of the bounce and then punches it into the gap wide of cover for a boundary
There's a man in the deep now
Azmatullah to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven in front of square on the off-side for a single
Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, no run, fuller length delivery on off, Fraser-McGurk looks to drive and skews a thick edge to backward point
Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, that's very sloppy, would've been a single, but Warrier overruns and allows a boundary - length ball on the pads and it was flicked behind square on the on-side
Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, no run, change of pace from Omarzai, slower ball outside off - Fraser-McGurk swipes and misses by a long way

Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, a complete misjudgement and Rashid has dropped a steepler - lots of luck already for Fraser-McGurk, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, Fraser-McGurk was early into the flick, closed the face of the bat and the big edge popped over mid-on - Rashid ran across, he did seem to have it under control, but then he got into an awkward position, had to turn around to complete the catch, makes a big mess of it
Sandeep Warrier, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, no run, on a good length and just outside off, punched straight to the fielder at cover-point
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, wide, banged in short and well down leg, Fraser-McGurk was shaping for the pull and missed, called as a wide
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, no run, low full-toss from Warrier, was the awayswinger, Fraser-McGurk backs away and can't beat cover with the drive
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, no run, back of a length and angling across the right-hander, Fraser-McGurk shapes for an ugly slog and misses
A slip in place

Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, hammered, back of a length and at the stumps, bowled at a friendly length, Fraser-McGurk picks it early, swivels across and then thumps the pull over deep backward square leg for a maximum, was a 93m hit

Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Fraser-McGurk, pitched up by Warrier - Fraser-McGurk clears his front leg and then hoists it over mid-on, couple of bounces and over the ropes
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, very full from Warrier, punched to the left of mid-on for a single
Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, short of a length and at the stumps, Fraser-McGurk swings hard and gets a thick under-edge past square leg for a single

Azmatullah to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, lovely, fraction short from Omarzai - Shaw picks the length early, swivels across and then pulls it over mid-on, almost went all the way, bouncing right in front of the ropes
Azmatullah to Prithvi Shaw, no run, much better from Omarzai, pitched up on off, Shaw opens himself and defends it back at the bowler
Azmatullah to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, length ball on the pads, clipped behind square on the on-side for a single
Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, no run, nicely bowled by Omarzai - spears in the yorker on leg, Fraser-McGurk cleared his front leg and gets an under-edge that rolls back off his boot to the bowler
Youngest to 100 IPL appearances 24y, 221d - Rashid Khan 24y 229d - Shubman Gill 25y, 182d - Virat Kohli 25y, 335d - Sanju Samson 26y, 108d - Piyush Chawla

Azmatullah to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, beautifully played, a mere chip, but the timing is so good that the ball sails over the mid-wicket ropes - full and at the pads, Fraser-McGurk shuffles across, brings his wrists into play and then clears the ground with a well timed stroke
Warrier to Prithvi Shaw, 1 run, a big leading edge, but the ball rolls through backward point, the awayswinger from Warrier and he opened up Shaw on the angle as he looked to work it onto the on-side
Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Warrier to Fraser-McGurk, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! The Fraser-McGurk show is over - he did strike it cleanly, but it came off the bottom of the bat, lots of height and straight down Noor's throat at deep square leg. Warrier deserved this wicket - bowled a seam-up ball and got it to angle into the right-hander, Fraser-McGurk did pick it up, brought his wrists into play and then watches in disbelief as the ball lobbed into the fielder's hands. Fraser-McGurk c Noor Ahmad b Warrier 23(14) [4s-2 6s-2]
Axar Patel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Warrier to Axar, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, Axar went hard on the drive and mistimed it to mid-off
Axar has been promoted to number 3
Warrier to Axar, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven to the left of mid-off for a single
Warrier to Prithvi Shaw, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Warrier to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! A superb diving catch from Noor, but is it a clean catch? He looks convinced, but the third umpire will have a look. Prithvi Shaw didn't go anywhere - looks like a fair catch, the fingers seem to be under the ball, but umpire Akshay Totre is checking for the side angle. Will Prithvi Shaw get away with the benefit of doubt. He's satisfied that the right hand is underneath the ball and that's good enough to send Prithvi Shaw on his way. Two wickets in the over for Warrier, two catches in the over for Noor and DC have lost both openers now. This is a proper catch though - banged in short and Shaw was slightly cramped for room on the pull, he swivelled across and went through with the shot, the ball always looked like it'd drop in front of Noor, but he ran in, dived sideways and ensured that he got his fingers under it. Prithvi Shaw c Noor Ahmad b Warrier 11(7) [4s-2]
Shai Hope, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Warrier to Shai Hope, no run, on a good length and just outside off, pushed back at the bowler
Azmatullah to Axar, no run, fuller length delivery from round the wicket, Axar went hard on the drive and mistimed it to the off-side
Azmatullah to Axar, 1 run, Omarzai drags the length back as Axar came down the track, punched in front of mid-off for a quick single
Azmatullah to Shai Hope, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven to the right of backward point where Shahruh dives and keeps them down to a single
Azmatullah to Axar, 1 run, banged in short and at the body, Axar swivels and under-edges the pull, behind square on the on-side for a single
Azmatullah to Shai Hope, FOUR, cracking shot, a low full-toss from Omarzai, Hope leans across and jams it back past the non-striker, splits the two men in the ring at mid-on and mid-off
Azmatullah to Shai Hope, no run, fuller length delivery on the pads, Hope fell across on the flick and misses, the ball rolling to the on-side off his pad
Warrier to Axar, no run, banged in short and following Axar as he backed away, he drops the gloves and sways away from the line
Warrier to Axar, 1 run, short of a good length and on off, dabbed in front of backward point for a single
Warrier to Shai Hope, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, Hope leans forward and finds cover with the punchy drive
Warrier to Shai Hope, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Warrier to Shai Hope, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! A big edge on the slog and Warrier has three wickets inside the powerplay. They've been catching well in this game - the Afghan pair, despite Rashid's drop earlier. On a good length and a hint of shape away from off, lured Hope into the big drive and he lost his shape in the process, slices it off the thick edge, high and over backward point, Rashid runs in from the deep, dives forward and completes a fine two-handed catch. DC have slipped badly in this batting PP. Shai Hope c Rashid Khan b Warrier 5(6) [4s-1]
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Warrier to Pant, no run, short and at the left-hander, Pant swivels across and finds short fine with the pull
Warrier to Pant, no run, Warrier shortens the length on off, dabbed with an angled bat to slip

Summary (Overs 1-6) > Fraser-McGurk dropped early by Rashid > Both openers get off to a quick start > Fraser-McGurk holes out for 23 off 14 > Noor takes a screamer to dismiss Shaw > Hope becomes Warrier’s 3rd victim
Azmatullah to Axar, no run, fuller length delivery on off, pushed back at the bowler
Azmatullah to Axar, no run, on a good length and just outside off, driven straight to the fielder at cover
STAT: This is just the third time Axar Patel is batting at No.3 in his T20 career, second time in the IPL. The previous instance was for PBKS against RCB in Indore in 2017.
Azmatullah to Axar, no run, short and at the left-hander, Axar's cramped for room and miscues the pull to mid-wicket

Azmatullah to Axar, FOUR, cracking shot, much needed for Axar, that'll relieve some pressure off him - on a good length and well wide of off, lets him free his arms and Axar crashes the drive wide of cover
Back to over the wicket
Azmatullah to Axar, leg byes, 1 run, low full-toss on the pads, Axar was shaping for the flick and missed, off the pad and rolled to long leg for a leg-bye
Azmatullah to Pant, no run, banged in short by Omarzai - Pant plays the half-arm jab and finds mid-wicket

Three wickets within the PP this season 3/14 - Trent Boult (RR) vs MI, Mumbai WS 3/15 - Sandeep Warrier (GT) vs DC, Delhi Three wickets within the PP for GT 4/7 - Mohammed Shami vs DC, Ahmedabad, 2023 3/10 - Mohammed Shami vs LSG, Mumbai WS, 2022 3/17 - Mohammed Shami vs SRH, Ahmedabad, 2023 3/15 - Sandeep Warrier vs DC, Delhi, 2024
One slip for Rashid
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rashid Khan to Axar, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Axar backs away and manages to skew an inside edge, behind square on the on-side for a single
Rashid Khan to Pant, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single

Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, appeal for LBW, but the ball might've pitched outside leg. They think and decide against a review, was pushed thrtough and Axar was beaten on the inside edge. Replays though show that he jammed a thick inside edge onto the front-pad
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, flighted delivery on off, extra bounce and Axar can only push it back at the bowler
Rashid Khan to Axar, SIX, lovely, the wrong 'un from Rashid, but Axar spotted it early, gets down low and then nails the slog-sweep, sending it high and into the stands at mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Axar, 2 runs, another wrong 'un from Rashid, but the length is short and it's punched square on the off-side for a couple mof runs
Spin from both ends and it's Noor
Noor Ahmad, comes into the attack

Noor Ahmad to Pant, FOUR, nicely played, a gentle start from Noor - dropped it short and down leg, Pant gets inside the line and then helps it on its way with the slog sweep, clears short fine and it's a one bounce boundary
Noor Ahmad to Pant, wide, pushed through by Noor, but he slips it down leg, Pant was looking to sweep and missed, called as a wide
Noor Ahmad to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery on off and middle, Pant backs away and pushes it into the gap wide of cover-point for a single
Noor Ahmad to Axar, 1 run, loopy delivery outside off, driven down to long-on for a single
Noor Ahmad to Pant, no run, tossed up and drifting into the left-hander, Pant was looking to flick and gets an inside edge onto the pad
Noor Ahmad to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, punched square on the off-side for a single
Noor Ahmad to Axar, 1 run, flatter and angling into the left-hander - Axar is cramped on the cut and manages to drag a thick inside edge to long-on
Time for the strategic break. Three wickets for Sandeep Warrier has put the Titans ahead, but Axar is in and he's joined by Pant, can DC recover in the next passage of play?
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, flighted delivery on middle, Axar backs away and just about jams it back at the bowler
Rashid Khan to Axar, 2 runs, tossed up around off, nudged behind square on the off-side and an overthrow allows a second run
Rashid Khan to Axar, FOUR, beautifully played, Rashid drags the length back, but it's tad too short and it's pulled powerfully past square leg, bisects the gap between the two men in the deep
Rashid Khan to Axar, 1 run, Rashid drops another short on off, pulled straighter and to the fielder at deep mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Pant, FOUR, hammered, Rashid has been way too short in this over - was the leg-break, but Pant rocks back and then drills the pull through square leg, no need to run for those
Rashid Khan to Pant, 1 run, Pant shimmies down the pitch to a well flighted delivery and works it to long-on for a single, 12 off the over

Noor Ahmad to Pant, no run, that was so well bowled by Noor - saw Pant coming down the track and pushed it wider of off, Pant had to reach out on the drive, squirts a thick inside edge and then has to rush back as the ball bounced towards the keeper
Noor Ahmad to Pant, SIX, beautifully played, tad too full from Noor - Pant gets down low, brings out the slog sweep and sends it sailing into the crowd at wide mid-wicket
Noor Ahmad to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, nudged in front of square on the on-side for a single
Noor Ahmad to Axar, FOUR, beautifully played, too full and too wide from Noor - Axar gets onto his knee, gets under the ball and then drills it over cover for a boundary
Noor Ahmad to Axar, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, dragged down to long-on for a single
Noor Ahmad to Pant, 1 run, the wrong 'un from Noor, but the length is short and it's punched wide of cover for a single, 13 off the over
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Mohit Sharma to Pant, FOUR, thumped, Pant is in some serious mood tonight - tad too short and just outside off, he picked the length early, swivelled across and then pulled it over square leg for a boundary
Mohit Sharma to Pant, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven in front of square on the off-side for a single
Mohit Sharma to Axar, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed off the back-foot to mid-off
Mohit Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower ball on off, Pant can't beat backward point with the open faced drive, just a single and that brings up DC's 100
Mohit Sharma to Axar, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, punched down to long-off for a single

Mohit Sharma to Pant, FOUR, nicely played, slower ball from Mohit, but the length is short and there's width on offer as well - Pant gets on top of the bounce and then scythes the cut, to the left of backward point for a boundary, 12 off the over
Summary (Overs 7-12) > Axar and Pant take things slow > GT spinners fail to make an impact > Both batters expand their range of shots > Scoring rate grows rapidly after a quiet period
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, tossed up on the pads, Axar was shaping for the paddle and missed, half-an-appeal for LBW, but that had pitched outside leg
Rashid Khan to Axar, FOUR, lovely, tad too short from Rashid - Patel makes room and then cuts it hard, into the gap wide of cover and scurries away to the ropes in a hurry
Rashid Khan to Axar, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, eased backward of square on the off-side for a single
Rashid Khan to Pant, no run, the wrong 'un from Rashid - Pant goes back and defends it back at the bowler
Rashid Khan to Pant, 1 run, tossed up on middle, muscled away off the back-foot, behind square on the on-side for a single
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, pushed through by Rashid - Axar backs away and jams it back at the bowler
More spin and it's Shahrukh Khan
Shahrukh Khan, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Shahrukh Khan to Pant, no run, tossed up on off, Pant gets half forward in defence
Shahrukh Khan to Pant, no run, flighted delivery on off, steered with an open face and Pant can't beat backward point
Shahrukh Khan to Pant, leg byes, 1 run, Shahrukh drifts one down leg, Pant was looking to sweep and gets an under-edge past the keeper
Shahrukh Khan to Axar, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Axar backs away and drives it square past cover for a single
Shahrukh Khan to Pant, 1 run, Pant comes down the wicket, takes the ball on the full and punches it to long-on for a single
The on-field umpire has a chat with Pant, not sure what happened though

Shahrukh Khan to Axar, SIX, that ruins the over for Shahrukh - flighted delivery on middle, Axar backed away, gets under the length and gets enough elevation on the lofted drive, high and wide of long-on, dropping over the ropes
Rashid Khan to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Pant backs away and cuts it square on the off-side for a single
Rashid Khan to Axar, 1 run, tossed up on off, Axar gets down low and drags the sweep to deep mid-wicket, just a single
Rashid, from round the wicket
Rashid Khan to Pant, 1 run, flatter delivery on middle-leg, Pant got down low and paddled it fine towards fine-leg, good work from the fielder there
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, length delivery on off-stump, Axar hangs back and punches it towards mid-off
Rashid Khan to Axar, no run, tossed up full on middle, Axar skips down the track looking to work it into the leg-side and yorks himself

Rashid Khan to Axar, FOUR, that's 50 for Axar! Dragged down just a touch on middle, Axar pressed back and heaved it away through to the deep mid-wicket fence to bring up his fifty, it's been a fine knock
Mohit Sharma [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, the helicopter took off there! Full and on the pads, Pant stood still and played a proper helicopter whip, timed it sweetly and it sailed over the cow corner fence!
Mohit Sharma to Pant, 1 run, slower delivery full and wide outside off, Pant waits for it and smacks it out to sweeper cover
Mohit Sharma to Axar, 2 runs, slower length delivery just outside off, Axar waits for it and punches it firmly to wide long-off, Miller the fielder does well to keep it down to two
Mohit Sharma to Axar, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Axar had to reach out as he dragged it towards mid-wicket with a mistimed pull
Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, launched into the stands! Full and just outside off, pace off but was in the slot, Pant watched it closely before giving it a proper whack to send it over long-off
Mohit Sharma to Pant, no run, slower short ball on middle, Pant got inside the line looking to pull it away fine and missed, the over ends with a dot
Timeout. Both these batters seem to have exploded out of nowhere. The acceleration couldn't have come at a better time for DC. Four overs to go and they'll be looking at a minimum of 180 from here.
Noor Ahmad [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack

Noor Ahmad to Axar, 1 run, that's the 100-run stand, very full on middle-leg, Axar skipped down the track looking to slog it away, got too close to it and got a thick inside edge that went towards deep square leg
Noor Ahmad to Pant, no run, flatter delivery just outside off, Pant hangs back and finds backward point with the cut
Noor Ahmad to Pant, 1 run, length delivery wide outside off, Pant reaches out and falls over as he whips it into the leg-side towards deep square leg
Noor Ahmad to Axar, SIX, a clean strike into the crowd! Full and just outside off, Axar leant in and smoked it clean over the cow corner ropes with a full swing of the blade, went high and far
Noor Ahmad to Axar, SIX, two in a row! Floated up full on off-stump, Axar pressed forward and lofted this through the line, great strike once more and it went straight back over the bowler
Noor Ahmad to Axar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Noor Ahmad to Axar, out Caught by Sai Kishore!! Looks to go a third time but that's the end of him! Flatter delivery on off-stump, wasn't quite full enough like the previous two, Axar slapped it hard and flat towards long-on, didn't hit it cleanly and the fielder there took it easily. Went flat and straight to him. GT needed that wicket. Axar c Sai Kishore b Noor Ahmad 66(43) [4s-5 6s-4]
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohit Sharma to Pant, 1 run, very full on off-stump, pushed down the ground to long-on

Mohit Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, Tristan Stubbs gets going straightaway! Length delivery just outside off, was pace off, Stubbs stood still and watched it closely before pulling it away firmly into the gap at cow corner, one-bounce four
Mohit Sharma to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, full just outside off, driven nicely down to wide long-off

Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, gets to his fifty in style! He gets a juicy full-toss on middle, he cleared his front-leg and slogged it away into the leg-side, didn't hit it all that cleanly but got enough to send it over the ropes at wide long-on
Mohit Sharma to Pant, no run, full and just outside off, Pant swings for the hills and misses

Mohit Sharma to Pant, 2 runs, length delivery pushed out wide outside off, Pant shuffled across and dragged it into the leg-side with a pull, one hand came off the bat and it went towards deep mid-wicket, Rashid kept it down to two with a slide
Very interesting decision here, Sai Kishore to bowl his first over and it's the 19th of the innings. Talk about high-pressure situations!
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Sai Kishore to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Tristan Stubbs reaches out and carves it out to deep extra cover
Sai Kishore to Pant, 1 run, floats out a low full-toss on the pads and gets away with it, Pant fell over as he looked to paddle-sweep it fine, couldn't beat the man at deep backward square leg
Sai Kishore to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, creamed right along the ground! Tossed up full and wide outside off, lot of width and Stubbs drilled it into the gap between deep extra cover and long-off

Sai Kishore to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, this one goes all the way! Floated up full and on the stumps, ended up being a juicy full-toss and Stubbs smoked it over the deep mid-wicket fence, just about got enough

Sai Kishore to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, another boundary! Flatter and quicker outside off this time, Stubbs watched it very closely again before slapping it hard into the gap between deep extra cover and long-off, brilliant batting!
Sai Kishore to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, the experiment costs GT and Gill! Tossed up full on middle, right in the slot this and you bet Stubbs smoked this out of the park, struck clean and over long-on

Mohit Sharma to Pant, 2 runs, great fielding in the deep, slower delivery full and just outside off, Pant gave it everything as he drilled it out towards deep cover, Sai Kishore stopped it with a dive to his left
Mohit Sharma to Pant, wide, length delivery pushed out wide outside off, Pant moved over a little but still too wide

Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, tipped over the bar! Low full-toss on off-stump, Pant swung hard again, bat turned in his hand and it went towards long-on, Shahrukh the fielder there, was a tough chance but he didn't time his jump, hit his fingertips and went over the ropes!

Mohit Sharma to Pant, FOUR, he's found the gap this time! Mohit Sharma went for a wide yorker, was a low full-toss past the tramline, Pant reached out as far as he could and stuck his bat out at it, managed to slice it right into the gap at deep backward point, one-bounce four
Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, there is no respite wherever you bowl! Banegd in short on middle, Pant shuffled across his stumps a touch and hooked it away over the deep backward square leg ropes
Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, high in the air and well over the ropes! Another full-toss on off-stump, Pant pressed forward and sent it into orbit over long-on! Very high and very far

Mohit Sharma to Pant, SIX, that's some finish to the innings! 31 runs off the last over! Another low full-toss on middle, Mohit Sharma just could not get his yorker right, Pant swiped it away over the deep square leg ropes!

21:12 Local Time, 15:42 GMT, 21:12 IST: Those last 30 minutes have gone horribly wrong for GT. The way Delhi started after being put into bat, it never looked like they'd get 200 let alone 220. Sandeep Warrier nipped out three in the powerplay and Axar, who was promoted to number 3, and Rishabh Pant were left to rebuild. They took their time to get their eye in and played out a few overs with caution. With GT's spinners coming on, they slowly started expanding their range of shots before Axar decided to floor the pedal around the 10th over. Axar was eventually dismissed for 66 - his highest IPL score but DC's scoring rate only kept going with Pant and Stubbs at the crease. It looked like DC would target around 180 but a gamble from GT to bowl Sai Kishore in the 19th over only helped the Capitals. That over went for 22 and the final over was the cherry on top as Pant picked off 31 runs off it. Massive chase coming up for GT.

Axar Patel - I think it's phenomenal effort. They're fantastic finishers (on Pant and Stubbs), that's what we talked about when we were in the middle. My role was to take on the three spinners, the talk was that we should take the partnership as deep as possible, the ball wasn't coming onto the bat, was a slow pitch. The mindset is very important, you can't think about playing off a bowler, the mindset was to be attacking, take the single and twos on offer and keep rotating the strike. We thought 170-180 would be a good score, so this (224 should be enough to win the match)
